comments: Dragic (BKN) moves alongside of and absorbs the marginal contact from Doncic (DAL) during his drive.
Dragic (BKN) moves laterally into Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and makes contact with his body, which affects his SQBR during the drive.
Finney-Smith (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the marginal contact from Durant (BKN) in the post.
Durant (BKN) and Finney-Smith (DAL) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs during the cut toward the perimeter.
Dragic (BKN) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs as he comes together with Doncic (DAL) during the rebound.
Durant (BKN) is in the paint for about three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Brown (BKN) and Doncic (DAL) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs off-ball, which does not affect Doncic's ability to get to the post entry pass.
Claxton (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Finney-Smith (DAL) engages with Durant (BKN) as he goes to set the pick and the contact is marginal as they quickly disengage.
Following the missed shot by Durant (BKN), Claxton (BKN) makes contact with the ball when it is not above the rim and within the imaginary cylinder.
Kleber (DAL) reaches for the ball and incidental contact occurs with Claxton's (BKN) hand after the release on his tip-shot attempt.
After the pick, Claxton (BKN) and Dinwiddie (DAL) briefly engage in marginal contact off ball prior to separating.
Dinwiddie (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Claxton's (BKN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dragic (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position on Doncic (DAL) during the drive.
Brown (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and firms up to absorb the contact during the pick.
Dinwiddie (DAL) contests Durant's (BKN) jump shot attempt and any follow-through contact after the release is deemed marginal.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Brown's (BKN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact during the pick.
Dragic (BKN) legally contests Dinwiddie's (DAL) jump shot attempt. Replay Center confirmed the ruling on the court that the shot was released prior to the game clock expiring.
